{"lemma":"وَزِيرٌ","slug":"وَزِيرٌ","root":"#.ز.ر","root_slug":"_-ز-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ز-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"وَزِير","root":"وزر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41906"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%B2%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"minister, cabinet minister"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vizier"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"helper, assistant"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"queen"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"The original attested meaning is “assistant”, and the political sense only arose in the Umayyad period. Likely related to the verb وَزَرَ (wazara, “to carry, to shoulder”) with the root و ز ر (w z r), meaning “someone who carries a burden”, but owing to the idea of assistance by handmen this may be denominal. Likely borrowed from an Iranian term surfacing as Middle Persian [script needed] (wcyl /⁠vičīr⁠/, “decision, judgment”), Avestan 𐬬𐬍𐬗𐬌𐬭𐬀 (vīcira, “arbitrator, judge”, literally “deciding, one who is taking or has made a decision”), Old Armenian վճիռ (včiṙ)."},"ipa":["/wa.ziːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41906","headword_ar":"وَزِيرٌ","root":"wzr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwaAzirN","text_ar":"مُوَازِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who bears"},{"kind":"text","text":"a burden or burdens"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who aids, assists"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"helps, and strengthens, another:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 3:] (S, A, K:) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^akiylN","text_ar":"اَكِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muw^aAkilN","text_ar":"مُوَاكِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaliysN","text_ar":"جَلِيسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mujaAlisN","text_ar":"مُجَالِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b2-  (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A vicegerent"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a king or the like: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a confidential minister of state:"},{"kind":"text","text":"in English commonly written"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vizier,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in imitation of the Turkish pronunciation; but properly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wezeer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"familiar"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the king,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who bears his master's burden, and aids him by his counsel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wzyr","text_ar":"وزير"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the king is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"person who bears with him"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuwaAziruhu","text_ar":"يُوَازِرُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yuHaAmiluhu","text_ar":"يُحَامِلُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the burdens of the regal office:"},{"kind":"text","text":"not from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwaAzarapN","text_ar":"مُوَازَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying the “ act of aiding or the like, ” because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this latter word is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the derivative from it of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aziyrN","text_ar":"اَزِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) ISd says, some hold that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wzyr","text_ar":"وزير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is substituted for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but Abu-l-'Abbás says, that this is not agreeable with analogy; for the substitution of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a word of this measure is rare, and that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more strange: (TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wzyr","text_ar":"وزير"},{"kind":"text","text":"is so called because he bears for the king the burden of administration: (S, * Msb:) or it is from ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wazarN","text_ar":"وَزَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", signifying “ a mountain to which one has recourse to save himself from destruction: ” so the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wzyr","text_ar":"وزير"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the khaleefeh is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one upon whose counsel the khaleefeh relies in his affairs, and to whom he betakes himself for refuge"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"safety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Is-hák, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wuzaraA='u","text_ar":"وُزَرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awozaArN","text_ar":"اَوْزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;) the latter like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$oraAfN","text_ar":"اَشْرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayotaAmN","text_ar":"اَيْتَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yatiymN","text_ar":"يَتِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}